@startuml
title Safehome Security System - State Diagram

state "Power On" as PowerOn
state "Startup Check" as StartupCheck
state "Problem During Startup" as ProblemDuringStartup
state "Ready to Use" as ReadyToUse
state "Resetting" as Resetting
state "Activating" as Activating
state "Turning Off" as TurningOff
state "Monitoring" as Monitoring
state "Alarm Triggered" as AlarmTriggered
state "False Alarm or Time Ended" as FalseAlarmOrTimeEnded
state "Normal" as Normal

PowerOn --> StartupCheck : Check Everything /\nIf Problem, Go to ProblemDuringStartup
StartupCheck --> ReadyToUse : No Problem, Continue
StartupCheck --> ProblemDuringStartup : Problem, Stop

ReadyToUse --> Resetting : User Requests Reset /\nReset System
ReadyToUse --> Activating : User Requests Activation /\nActivate System
ReadyToUse --> TurningOff : User Requests Shutdown /\nTurn Off System

Activating --> Monitoring : Successfully Activated /\nStart Monitoring
Monitoring --> AlarmTriggered : Sensor Triggered /\nStart Alarm, Send Alerts
AlarmTriggered --> FalseAlarmOrTimeEnded : False Alarm or Time Ended /\nContinue Monitoring
FalseAlarmOrTimeEnded --> Monitoring : Continue Monitoring
Monitoring --> Normal : User Enters Password /\nReturn to Normal
@enduml
